plication/problem+json":{"schema":{"$ref":"#/components/schemas/ProblemDetail"}}}},"400":{"description":"Bad Request","content":{"application/problem+json":{"schema":{"$ref":"#/components/schemas/ProblemDetail"}}}},"500":{"description":"Internal Server Error.","content":{"application/problem+json":{"schema":{"$ref":"#/components/schemas/ProblemDetail"}}}},"200":{"description":"OK","content":{"text/csv":{"schema":{"type":"string"}}}}}},"post":{"tags":["Feed Management API"],"summary":"Upload the domains to the feed","description":"The Upload API is responsible for updating a feed which could include adding and deleting a list of domains contained in CSV format.\n\n## Upload Types\n### Incremental\nUpdates the feed incrementally with the data provided in the CSV.\n\nThe CSV file for this operation requires two columns, 'domain' and 'action'.\nThe two supported actions are 'add' and 'delete'\n\n**Sample Incremental CSV file Content**\n```\ndomain,action\nthreat_abc.com,add\nthreat_def.com,delete\n```\n\n### Overwrite\nOverwrites the existing feed with the data provided in the CSV.\n\nThe CSV file for this operation requires one column, 'domain'.\n\n**Sample Overwrite CSV file Content**\n```\ndomain\nthreat_abc.com\nthreat_def.com\n```\n\n## Few points related to processing\nIf there are multiple rows for the same domain in the uploaded CSV,\nonly the last one will be processed and rest will be ignored.\n","operationId":"uploadElements","parameters":[{"name":"feedId","in":"path","required":true,"schema":{"type":"string"}},{"name":"uploadType","in":"query","description":"Upload operation type","required":true,"schema":{"type":"string","description":"Upload operation type","enum":["INCREMENTAL","OVERWRITE"]}}],"requestBody":{"content":{"multipart/form-data":{"schema":{"required":["file"],"type":"object","properties":{"file":{"type":"string","description":"CSV file in the format as per the upload type","format":"binary"}}}}}},"responses":{"401":{"description":"Invalid auth